        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-02-11 20:10:43.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\nThanks for the commit message.  It make it clear the issue you are trying to protect against. \n\nIt seems safe to me to add a lock from keep notify and delete from happening at the same time.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "5f42503be6350ddb8919ecf26b81512eb0e28bad",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 256,
        "name": "Hiroya Nozaki",
        "email": "nozaki.hiroya@jp.fujitsu.com",
        "username": "HiroyaNozaki"
      },
      "date": "2013-02-12 02:18:58.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nYes, that can be true. Actually I'm thinking now that I should add a semaphore into lov_getref and lov_putref to confirm that there's no notify op when add and del ops, and that there's no add and del ops beside itself. But in this case, I cannot help adding an extra argument into obd_getref and putref .. like obd_getref(struct obd_device *, int rw) to get an rw_semaphore in a proper mode such as read mode or write mode. But ... it looks a bit awkward to me, doesn't it ?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
